				    <h1><a name="ShutdownScheduler-ShuttingDownaScheduler"></a>Shutting Down a Scheduler</h1>

<p><br clear="all" /></p>

<div class="code"><div class="codeHeader"><b>Wait for Executing Jobs to Finish</b></div><div class="codeContent">
<pre class="code-java"><span class="code-comment">//shutdown() does not <span class="code-keyword">return</span> until executing Jobs complete execution
</span>scheduler.shutdown(<span class="code-keyword">true</span>);</pre>
</div></div>

<div class="code"><div class="codeHeader"><b>Do Not Wait for Executing Jobs to Finish</b></div><div class="codeContent">
<pre class="code-java"><span class="code-comment">//shutdown() returns immediately, but executing Jobs <span class="code-keyword">continue</span> running to completion
</span>scheduler.shutdown();
<span class="code-comment">//or
</span>scheduler.shutdown(<span class="code-keyword">false</span>);</pre>
</div></div>

                    			    </td>
